Re: A few suggestions

Bitcointalk

2009-12-12 17:52:44 UTC - [11]Original Post

   The average total coins generated across the network per day stays the
   same.  Faster machines just get a larger share than slower machines.
   If everyone bought faster machines, they wouldnʼt get more coins than
   before.
   We should have a gentlemanʼs agreement to postpone the GPU arms race as
   long as we can for the good of the network.  Itʼs much easer to get new
   users up to speed if they donʼt have to worry about GPU drivers and
   compatibility.  Itʼs nice how anyone with just a CPU can compete fairly
   equally right now.
